#| msgid ""
#| "Anomen and <CHARNAME> continued adventuring until they were known as heroes "
#| "almost everywhere they went.  Many were the grand tales of the Shining "
#| "Knight and his utter devotion to his great lady.  <CHARNAME>'s past as the "
#| "terrible Bhaalspawn was forgotten forever as new deeds replaced old and a "
#| "legacy was created that far outstripped anything granted by godly blood.  So"
#| " prolific were their careers that the proposed date of their wedding kept "
#| "getting moved back, either due to impending crisis or some lucrative "
#| "adventure that one or the other would insist on investigating. Finally a "
#| "date approached that both <CHARNAME> and her beloved were determined to "
#| "keep, and the much heralded event drew heroes and dignitaries from across "
#| "FaerÃ»n. The couple had touched the lives of many, and those people arrived "
#| "in droves to watch Elminster himself unite the two in one of the grandest "
#| "ceremonies the city of Baldur's Gate had ever seen. Anomen and <CHARNAME> "
#| "retired from public life shortly after the celebrated birth of their "
#| "daughter, although if tales be true, their adventures never truly ended.  "
#| "Anomen would rise high in the hierarchy of his church, and <CHARNAME> would "
#| "continue to be the center of strange events throughout their lives.  So, "
#| "too, would their daughter, tutored by two of the greatest heroes in the "
#| "Realms, forge a legend to rival that of her mother's.  That, however, is "
#| "another story completely..."
msgid ""
"Anomen and <CHARNAME> continued adventuring until they were known as heroes "
"almost everywhere they went. Many were the grand tales of the Shining Knight"
" and his utter devotion to his great lady. <CHARNAME>'s past as the terrible"
" Bhaalspawn was forgotten forever as new deeds replaced old and a legacy was"
" created that far outstripped anything granted by godly blood. So prolific "
"were their careers that the proposed date of their wedding kept getting "
"moved back, either due to impending crisis or some lucrative adventure that "
"one or the other would insist on investigating. Finally a date approached "
"that both <CHARNAME> and her beloved were determined to keep, and the much "
"heralded event drew heroes and dignitaries from across Faerûn. The couple "
"had touched the lives of many, and those people arrived in droves to watch "
"Elminster himself unite the two in one of the grandest ceremonies the city "
"of Baldur's Gate had ever seen. Anomen and <CHARNAME> retired from public "
"life shortly after the celebrated birth of their daughter, although if tales"
" be true, their adventures never truly ended. Anomen would rise high in the "
"hierarchy of his church, and <CHARNAME> would continue to be the center of "
"strange events throughout their lives. So, too, would their daughter, "
"tutored by two of the greatest heroes in the Realms, forge a legend to rival"
" that of her mother's. That, however, is another story completely..."
msgstr ""
"Anomen und <CHARNAME> führten ihr Abenteurerleben fort, bis sie schließlich "
"überall, wohin sie auch kamen, bekannt waren.  Die großartigen Geschichten "
"um den strahlenden Ritter und die völlige Hingabe zu seiner großen Liebe "
"waren zahlreich.  <CHARNAME>s Vergangenheit als Bhaalbrut war für immer "
"vergessen, als neue Taten die alten ersetzten und eine Legende geschaffen "
"wurde, welche die durch göttliches Blut gewährte bei weitem überflügeln "
"sollte.  Ihr Leben war derart ausgefüllt, dass der vorgesehene Termin für "
"ihre Hochzeit ein ums andere Mal verschoben werden musste, weil einer der "
"beiden eine drohende Krise abwenden oder ein einzigartiges Abenteuer "
"bestehen wollte.  Schließlich jedoch nahte der Tag, den sich sowohl "
"<CHARNAME> als auch ihr Geliebter gesetzt hatten, und das groß angekündigte "
"Ereignis zog Helden und Würdenträger aus ganz Faerûn nach Baldurs Tor.  Das "
"Brautpaar hatte das Leben vieler in irgendeiner Art beeinflusst, und sie "
"kamen in Scharen, als Elminster selbst die beiden in der großartigsten "
"Zeremonie, die Baldurs Tor jemals gesehen hatte, vereinigte.  Kurze Zeit "
"später zogen sich Anomen und <CHARNAME> aus dem öffentlichen Leben zurück, "
"um die Geburt ihrer Tochter zu feiern.  Falls aber die Legenden stimmen, sie"
" haben ihre Abenteuer niemals wirklich geendet.  Anomen stieg im Laufe "
"seines Lebens hoch auf in der Hierarchie seiner Kirche, und <CHARNAME> stand"
" noch oft im Mittelpunkt seltsamer Ereignisse.  Und auch ihre Tochter, "
"großgezogen von zwei der größten Helden in den Reichen, formte eine Legende,"
" die der ihrer Mutter in nichts nachstehen sollte.  Dieses aber ist eine "
"vollkommen andere Geschichte..."

#: ascension_ee.tra:82715
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "Aerie and <CHARNAME> would prove inseparable, continuing their adventuring "
#| "for many years into the future.  Aerie's zest for travel brought the pair "
#| "over much of FaerÃ»n and even further.  Their young son was always in tow, "
#| "making <CHARNAME> smile with his wide-eyed awe at the wonders of the world."
#| "  Eventually the pair would settle, subsequently giving birth to a beautiful"
#| " daughter that was the second joy of their lives.  Only rarely would trouble"
#| " cause <CHARNAME> and Aerie to bring their great power to bear against the "
#| "evil of the world, though the tales of their battles would become legendary."
#| "  Their later years would hold one last great trek, as Aerie still felt a "
#| "sadness from her time of enslavement and the loss of her wings.  Together "
#| "she and <CHARNAME> sought the Avariel of Faenya-Dail, the winged elves she "
#| "was stolen from so long ago.  They discovered not only her people, but "
#| "loving parents that had spent years searching for their lost child.  Aerie "
#| "had finally found her family.  With no more mystery or confusion to cloud "
#| "their lives, it was there, among the clouds, that Aerie and <CHARNAME> would"
#| " finally be married.  Their union, it is said, was blessed by the presence "
#| "of Aerdrie Faenya and Baervan Wildwanderer both.  As for the children of "
#| "<CHARNAME> and Aerie, tutored by two of the Realm's most powerful beings, "
#| "their own destiny would be a tale to rival their father's..."
msgid ""
"Aerie and <CHARNAME> would prove inseparable, continuing their adventuring "
"for many years into the future. Aerie's zest for travel brought the pair "
"over much of Faerûn and even further. Their young son was always in tow, "
"making <CHARNAME> smile with his wide-eyed awe at the wonders of the world. "
"Eventually the pair would settle, subsequently giving birth to a beautiful "
"daughter that was the second joy of their lives. Only rarely would trouble "
"cause <CHARNAME> and Aerie to bring their great power to bear against the "
"evil of the world, though the tales of their battles would become legendary."
" Their later years would hold one last great trek, as Aerie still felt a "
"sadness from her time of enslavement and the loss of her wings. Together she"
" and <CHARNAME> sought the Avariel of Faenya-Dail, the winged elves she was "
"stolen from so long ago. They discovered not only her people, but loving "
"parents that had spent years searching for their lost child. Aerie had "
"finally found her family. With no more mystery or confusion to cloud their "
"lives, it was there, among the clouds, that Aerie and <CHARNAME> would "
"finally be married. Their union, it is said, was blessed by the presence of "
"Aerdrie Faenya and Baervan Wildwanderer both. As for the children of "
"<CHARNAME> and Aerie, tutored by two of the Realm's most powerful beings, "
"their own destiny would be a tale to rival their father's..."
msgstr ""
"Aerie und <CHARNAME> wurden unzertrennlich und setzen ihr Abenteurerleben "
"eine ganze Zeit lang fort.  Aeries Lust am Reisen brachte das Paar bis an "
"die Grenzen Faerûns und weit darüber hinaus.  Ihr junger Sohn war immer mit "
"dabei und wenn er mit weit aufgerissenen Augen die Wunder dieser Welt "
"bestaunte, so zauberte dieses ein Lächeln auf <CHARNAME>s Gesicht.  "
"Schließlich ließ sich das Paar nieder, eine wunderschöne Tochter wurde "
"geboren, welche die zweite Freude ihres Lebens wurde.  Selten nur brachte "
"Ärger <CHARNAME> und Aerie dazu, ihre ungeheure Macht aufzubringen, um das "
"Böse der Welt in seine Schranken zu weisen, trotzdem aber sollten ihre "
"Kämpfe Legende werden.  Ihre späteren Jahre sollten ein letztes großes "
"Abenteuer bereithalten, als Aerie wieder die Traurigkeit aus der Zeit der "
"Sklaverei und dem Verlust ihrer Flügel spürte.  Zusammen mit <CHARNAME> "
"suchte sie die Avariel von Faenya-Dail auf, ihr Volk der geflügelten Elfen, "
"dem sie vor so langer Zeit entrissen wurde.  Und sie fand nicht nur ihr Volk"
" sondern auch ihre lieben Eltern, die Jahre mit der Suche nach ihrem "
"verlorenen Kind verbracht hatten.  So fand Aerie schließlich doch noch ihre "
"Familie.  Jetzt, da es keine Verwirrung und keine Rätsel mehr für Aerie gab,"
" konnten Sie und <CHARNAME> endlich dort oben in den Wolken heiraten. Ihre "
"Vermählung, so sagt man, wurde durch die Anwesenheit sowohl von Aerdrie "
"Faenya als auch Baervan Wildwanderer gesegnet.  Und das Leben der Kinder von"
" <CHARNAME> und Aerie, aufgezogen von zwei der mächtigsten Wesen in den "
"Reichen, wurde ebenfalls zur Legende, welche sich nicht hinter der ihres "
"Vaters verstecken musste..."

#: balth.tra:1060
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "I wish I could take the credit for this ruse, <CHARNAME>.  But it seems I "
#| "was not the only member of the Five who plotted the downfall of the others."
msgid ""
"I wish I could take the credit for this ruse, <CHARNAME>. But it seems I was"
" not the only member of the Five who plotted the downfall of the others."
msgstr ""
"Ich wünschte, ich hätte die Lorbeeren für diese List verdient, <CHARNAME>.  "
"Aber es scheint, als sei ich nicht das einzige Mitglied der Fünf gewesen, "
"das den Untergang der anderen geplant hätte."

#: balth.tra:1072
msgid ""
"You won't be the first to try and kill me... and probably not the last!"
msgstr ""
"Ihr seid nicht der Erste, der versucht, mich zu töten... und wohl auch nicht"
" der Letzte!"

#: balth.tra:1074
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "It is true.  You are a good <PRO_MANWOMAN>, <CHARNAME>, and your stance "
#| "against evil is without question.  Your fight against the taint of our evil "
#| "father is worthy of praise."
msgid ""
"It is true. You are a good <PRO_MANWOMAN>, <CHARNAME>, and your stance "
"against evil is without question. Your fight against the taint of our evil "
"father is worthy of praise."
msgstr ""
"Es ist wahr.  Ihr seid ein gut<PRO_MANWOMAN>, <CHARNAME>, und Eure Haltung "
"gegen das Böse steht außer Frage.  Euer Kampf gegen den Makel unseres bösen "
"Vaters ist hoch zu loben."

#: balth.tra:1075
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "I sense no innate goodness within you, <CHARNAME>...though your deeds are "
#| "hailed far and wide as above reproach.  It is... interesting that one like "
#| "you who must struggle so much with our father's taint inside <PRO_HIMHER> "
#| "has done so much to fight true evil."
msgid ""
"I sense no innate goodness within you, <CHARNAME>...though your deeds are "
"hailed far and wide as above reproach. It is... interesting that one like "
"you who must struggle so much with our father's taint inside <PRO_HIMHER> "
"has done so much to fight true evil."
msgstr ""
"Ich spüre nichts davon, dass Ihr von Geburt aus gut wärt, <CHARNAME>... "
"obwohl Eure Taten in Nah und Fern als über jeden Vorwurf erhaben gepriesen "
"werden.  Es ist... interessant, dass jemand wie Ihr, der so sehr gegen den "
"Makel unseres Vaters im Inneren ankämpfen muss, so viel getan hat, das Böse "
"zu bekämpfen."

#: balth.tra:1076
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "I see the good that is within you, <CHARNAME>, but your deeds are hardly "
#| "above reproach.  I sense only a soul that struggles with our father's taint,"
#| " that struggles to find the good path where none exists."
msgid ""
"I see the good that is within you, <CHARNAME>, but your deeds are hardly "
"above reproach. I sense only a soul that struggles with our father's taint, "
"that struggles to find the good path where none exists."
msgstr ""
"Ich sehe das Gute in Eurem Inneren, <CHARNAME>, aber Eure Taten sind kaum "
"ohne Widersprüche.  Ich spüre nur eine Seele, die gegen den Makel unseres "
"Vaters ankämpft, die darum kämpft, den Weg des Guten zu finden, der nicht "
"existiert."

#: balth.tra:1077
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "I sense no innate goodness within you, <CHARNAME>.  I do not think your "
#| "deeds above reproach.  I sense only a soul struggling against the taint of "
#| "<PRO_HISHER> father, much like mine own."
msgid ""
"I sense no innate goodness within you, <CHARNAME>. I do not think your deeds"
" above reproach. I sense only a soul struggling against the taint of "
"<PRO_HISHER> father, much like mine own."
msgstr ""
"Ich spüre nichts davon, dass Ihr von Geburt aus gut wärt, <CHARNAME>.  Eure "
"Taten sind nicht ohne Widersprüche.  Ich spüre nur eine Seele, die gegen den"
" Makel ihres bösen Vaters ankämpft, so wie ich selbst."

#: balth.tra:1078
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "Actually, I am the perfect person to judge, <CHARNAME>.  I, too, contain the"
#| " taint of our father within me.  I, too, have felt its yearnings for blood, "
#| "its efforts to exert chaos upon my life.  I have mastered it... but only "
#| "barely.  Too well I know what it is capable of."
msgid ""
"Actually, I am the perfect person to judge, <CHARNAME>. I, too, contain the "
"taint of our father within me. I, too, have felt its yearnings for blood, "
"its efforts to exert chaos upon my life. I have mastered it... but only "
"barely. Too well I know what it is capable of."
msgstr ""
"Tatsächlich aber bin ich hier der beste Richter, <CHARNAME>.  Auch ich "
"besitze den Makel unseres Vaters in meinem Inneren.  Auch ich habe sein "
"Verlangen nach Blut gespürt, seine Versuche, mein Leben ins Chaos zu "
"stürzen. Ich habe es bezwungen... aber nur knapp.  Zu gut weiß ich, wozu es "
"im Stande ist."

#: balth.tra:1079
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "Naturally.  Our taint brings us no peace, does it, <CHARNAME>?  We fight in "
#| "self-defense and yet still we kill, still we bring destruction.  We may "
#| "claim an absence of responsibility, should we desire, but I know all too "
#| "well what the taint in our soul is capable of.  Only barely do I keep it "
#| "mastered."
msgid ""
"Naturally. Our taint brings us no peace, does it, <CHARNAME>? We fight in "
"self-defense and yet still we kill, still we bring destruction. We may claim"
" an absence of responsibility, should we desire, but I know all too well "
"what the taint in our soul is capable of. Only barely do I keep it mastered."
msgstr ""
"Natürlich.  Unser Makel bringt uns keinen Frieden, oder, <CHARNAME>?  Wir "
"kämpfen aus Notwehr, und doch töten wir, und doch bringen wir Zerstörung.  "
"Wir können die Verantwortung von uns schieben, wenn wir das wollen, aber nur"
" zu gut weiß ich, wozu der Makel in unserer Seele fähig ist.  Nur knapp kann"
" ich ihn beherrschen."

#: balth.tra:1080
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "I would expect no other response from a true <PRO_BROTHERSISTER> of mine.  I"
#| " know too well the thirst for death that comes with the taint of our sire.  "
#| "I have mastered it, but only barely... I pity those who are a slave to it."
msgid ""
"I would expect no other response from a true <PRO_BROTHERSISTER> of mine. I "
"know too well the thirst for death that comes with the taint of our sire. I "
"have mastered it, but only barely... I pity those who are a slave to it."
msgstr ""
"Ich hätte keine andere Antwort von einem wahren Bruder erwartet.  Ich kenne "
"nur zu gut den Durst nach Tod, der mit dem Makel unseres Erzeugers kommt.  "
"Ich habe ihn bezwungen, aber nur knapp... ich bedaure die, die seine Sklaven"
" sind."

#: balth.tra:1081
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "Do not make me laugh, <CHARNAME>.  If you expect me to believe that your "
#| "depraved existence exists to fight against evil in this world, then you "
#| "expect far too much."
msgid ""
"Do not make me laugh, <CHARNAME>. If you expect me to believe that your "
"depraved existence exists to fight against evil in this world, then you "
"expect far too much."
msgstr ""
"Bringt mich nicht zum Lachen, <CHARNAME>.  Wenn Ihr erwartet, dass ich "
"glaube, Eure armselige Existenz würde auf der Welt sein, um gegen das Böse "
"zu kämpfen, dann erwartet Ihr viel zu viel."

#: balth.tra:1082
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "But regardless of our wishes on the matter, our destiny has been written for"
#| " us, <CHARNAME>.  Some may run from it or deny it, while others embrace "
#| "it... but each and every Bhaalspawn has a seed within them that has sprung "
#| "forth a fruit laden with blood and murder.  Do you deny this?"
msgid ""
"But regardless of our wishes on the matter, our destiny has been written for"
" us, <CHARNAME>. Some may run from it or deny it, while others embrace it..."
" but each and every Bhaalspawn has a seed within them that has sprung forth "
"a fruit laden with blood and murder. Do you deny this?"
msgstr ""
"Aber was auch immer unsere Wünsche sein mögen in dieser Sache, unser "
"Schicksal ist für uns geschrieben, <CHARNAME>.  Manche mögen vor ihm "
"fliehen, manche mögen es verleugnen, manche mit Freude umarmen... aber jede "
"Bhaalbrut ist ein Samen gewesen, der eine Frucht von Blut und Mord "
"hervorgebracht hat.  Oder streitet Ihr das ab?"

#: balth.tra:1083
msgid "Are you implying that you are somehow different, Balthazar?"
msgstr "Wollt Ihr damit sagen, Ihr seid irgendwie anders, Balthasar?"

#: balth.tra:1084
msgid "I have only ever acted when it was necessary, in self-defense."
msgstr "Ich habe nur gehandelt, wenn es notwendig war, in Notwehr."

#: balth.tra:1085
msgid ""
"You would make us out to be victims of circumstance rather than masters of "
"our own destiny."
msgstr ""
"Also behauptet Ihr, wir wären eher Opfer der Umstände als Herren unseres "
"eigenen Schicksals."

#: balth.tra:1086
#, fuzzy
#| msgid "I deny nothing.  Death comes for all who stand in my way."
msgid "I deny nothing. Death comes for all who stand in my way."
msgstr ""
"Ich streite nichts ab.  Der Tod kommt zu allen, die mir im Weg stehen."

#: balth.tra:1087
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "I am death incarnate, fool!  Not some weak fool wrapped in denial like "
#| "yourself!"
msgid ""
"I am death incarnate, fool! Not some weak fool wrapped in denial like "
"yourself!"
msgstr ""
"Ich bin der fleischgewordene Tod, Ihr Narr!  Nicht ein schwacher Dummkopf "
"wie Ihr, der sich in Verleugnung hüllt!"

#: balth.tra:1088
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "I have little doubt that you know whereof I speak.  The taint is strong "
#| "within you... stronger than any single other spawn of our sire that I have "
#| "seen.  You have felt the dreams, the urges, have you not?  The chaos that is"
#| " your destiny has ripped wantonly through your life, regardless of your "
#| "wishes, has it not?  Do you deny that you bring violence and destruction "
#| "wherever you go, <CHARNAME>?"
msgid ""
"I have little doubt that you know whereof I speak. The taint is strong "
"within you... stronger than any single other spawn of our sire that I have "
"seen. You have felt the dreams, the urges, have you not? The chaos that is "
"your destiny has ripped wantonly through your life, regardless of your "
"wishes, has it not? Do you deny that you bring violence and destruction "
"wherever you go, <CHARNAME>?"
msgstr ""
"Ich habe kaum Zweifel, dass Ihr wisst, wovon ich spreche.  Der Makel ist "
"stark in Euch... stärker als in jedem anderen Nachkommen unseres Erzeugers, "
"den ich je gesehen habe.  Ihr habt die Träume gespürt, das Drängen, oder? "
"Das Chaos, das Euer Schicksal ist, ist mutwillig durch Euer Leben gestürmt, "
"ohne Eure Wünsche zu beachten, nicht wahr?  Leugnet Ihr, dass Ihr Gewalt und"
" Zerstörung bringt, wohin Ihr auch geht, <CHARNAME>?"

#: balth.tra:1089
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "I am nothing like you.  I exist to fight against the chaos of my taint, to "
#| "fight against the evil that Bhaal's legacy brings to this world.  I have "
#| "faced the evil within me and I have mastered it."
msgid ""
"I am nothing like you. I exist to fight against the chaos of my taint, to "
"fight against the evil that Bhaal's legacy brings to this world. I have "
"faced the evil within me and I have mastered it."
msgstr ""
"Ich bin nicht wie Ihr.  Ich existiere, um gegen das Chaos meines Makels zu "
"kämpfen, um zu kämpfen gegen das Böse, das Bhaals Erbe dieser Welt bringt.  "
"Ich habe mich dem Bösen in mir gestellt, und ich habe es bezwungen."

#: balth.tra:1090
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "No.  I have brought my share of death and destruction to this land.  But I "
#| "see a larger purpose behind it... I seek to end the possibility of Bhaal's "
#| "return forever, and to wipe his taint from the land."
msgid ""
"No. I have brought my share of death and destruction to this land. But I see"
" a larger purpose behind it... I seek to end the possibility of Bhaal's "
"return forever, and to wipe his taint from the land."
msgstr ""
"Nein. ich habe meinen Teil an Tod und Zerstörung über dieses Land gebracht."
"  Aber ich sehe einen höheren Zweck dahinter... Ich strebe danach, die "
"Rückkehr Bhaals ein für alle Mal unmöglich zu machen und seinen Makel von "
"diesem Land zu tilgen."

#: balth.tra:1091
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "I have mastered the power within me and held the evil in check, but I know "
#| "as well... if not better... then most of my brethren the threat that it "
#| "holds for all of FaerÃ»n.  I will not allow this.  I have dedicated my life "
#| "to preventing it."
msgid ""
"I have mastered the power within me and held the evil in check, but I know "
"as well... if not better... then most of my brethren the threat that it "
"holds for all of Faerun. I will not allow this. I have dedicated my life to "
"preventing it."
msgstr ""
"Ich habe die Macht in mir bezwungen und das Böse in Schach gehalten, aber "
"ich kenne genauso gut... wenn nicht besser... als meine Geschwister die "
"Gefahr, die es für ganz Faerûn darstellt.  Ich werde das nicht erlauben.  "
"Dies zu verhindern, ist der Sinn meines Lebens."

#: balth.tra:1092
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "If only we had met under other circumstances, <CHARNAME>...I would have "
#| "liked to sit and compare the paths that have brought us to this point.  If "
#| "we had not been forced by destiny to bear this taint upon our souls, what "
#| "would have become of us?  I regret what I must do, yet I know it must be "
#| "done."
msgid ""
"If only we had met under other circumstances, <CHARNAME>...I would have "
"liked to sit and compare the paths that have brought us to this point. If we"
" had not been forced by destiny to bear this taint upon our souls, what "
"would have become of us? I regret what I must do, yet I know it must be "
"done."
msgstr ""
"Wenn wir uns nur unter anderen Umständen begegnet wären, <CHARNAME>... wäre "
"es angenehm gewesen, nebeneinander zu sitzen und die Wege zu vergleichen, "
"die uns an diesen Punkt gebracht haben.  Wenn wir nicht vom Schicksal "
"gezwungen worden wären, diesen Makel in unseren Seelen zu tragen; was wäre "
"aus uns geworden?  Ich bedaure, was ich tun muss, aber ich weiß, dass ich es"
" tun muss."

#: balth.tra:1093
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "And what becomes of Melissan, then?  Is she free to raise Bhaal and complete"
#| " her plans?"
msgid ""
"And what becomes of Melissan, then? Is she free to raise Bhaal and complete "
"her plans?"
msgstr ""
"Und was wird dann aus Melissan?  Ist sie frei, Bhaal auferstehen zu lassen "
"und ihre Pläne zu vollenden?"

#: balth.tra:1094
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "You don't have to do this, Balthazar.  We don't have to fight each other."
msgid ""
"You don't have to do this, Balthazar. We don't have to fight each other."
msgstr ""
"Ihr müsst das nicht tun, Balthasar.  Wir müssen einander nicht bekämpfen."

#: balth.tra:1095
msgid ""
"You don't honestly see yourself as the force of righteousness in all this, "
"do you?"
msgstr ""
"Ihr glaubt doch nicht etwa wirklich, Ihr wärt hier der Verteidiger der "
"Rechtschaffenheit?"

#: balth.tra:1096
#, fuzzy
#| msgid "Enough talk, then.  Let's get this over with."
msgid "Enough talk, then. Let's get this over with."
msgstr "Genug Gerede also.  Lasst uns das hier beenden."

#: balth.tra:1097
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "Of course not.  It is she that holds the key to Bhaal's resurrection.  After"
#| " you are dead, she too must be destroyed."
msgid ""
"Of course not. It is she that holds the key to Bhaal's resurrection. After "
"you are dead, she too must be destroyed."
msgstr ""
"Natürlich nicht.  Sie ist es, die den Schlüssel zu Bhaals Wiederauferstehung"
" hält.  Wenn Ihr tot seid, muss auch sie zerstört werden."

#: balth.tra:1098
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "Then we should fight her together!  How do you know she still can't summon "
#| "Bhaal... everything you've fought for will be for nothing!"
msgid ""
"Then we should fight her together! How do you know she still can't summon "
"Bhaal... everything you've fought for will be for nothing!"
msgstr ""
"Dann sollten wir sie gemeinsam bekämpfen!  Wie wollt Ihr wissen, ob sie "
"nicht dennoch Bhaal herbeirufen kann... alles, wofür Ihr gekämpft habt, "
"würde sinnlos gewesen sein!"

#: balth.tra:1099
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "And you're going to stop her alone?  Have you given any thought to the fact "
#| "that maybe you've been helping her all along, that she's been playing you "
#| "like a harp?"
msgid ""
"And you're going to stop her alone? Have you given any thought to the fact "
"that maybe you've been helping her all along, that she's been playing you "
"like a harp?"
msgstr ""
"Und Ihr wollt sie allein aufhalten?  Habt Ihr je daran gedacht, dass Ihr ihr"
" vielleicht die ganze Zeit geholfen habt, dass sie auf Euch gespielt hat wie"
" auf einer Harfe?"

#: balth.tra:1100
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "Yet another death added to your tally?  And what then, once you kill her?  "
#| "Once you have all that power and it's yours alone... you think you're going "
#| "to resist that?"
msgid ""
"Yet another death added to your tally? And what then, once you kill her? "
"Once you have all that power and it's yours alone... you think you're going "
"to resist that?"
msgstr ""
"Noch ein weiterer Tod auf Eurer Rechnung?  Und was dann, wenn Ihr sie "
"getötet habt?  Wenn Ihr all diese Macht habt, und sie gehört nur Euch "
"allein... denkt Ihr, Ihr würdet ihr widerstehen?"

#: balth.tra:1101
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "What makes you think you could kill her?  I'm the one that has defeated all "
#| "the Bhaalspawn... while you were doing nothing but hiding in this fortress "
#| "making the peasants miserable."
msgid ""
"What makes you think you could kill her? I'm the one that has defeated all "
"the Bhaalspawn... while you were doing nothing but hiding in this fortress "
"making the peasants miserable."
msgstr ""
"Wie kommt Ihr darauf, ihr könntet sie töten?  Ich habe alle Bhaalbrut "
"besiegt... während Ihr nichts getan habt als Euch in dieser Festung zu "
"verkriechen und die Dorfbewohner zu terrorisieren."

#: balth.tra:1102
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "I thought you were going to kill yourself after I was dead.  Sure you won't "
#| "see some more evil once Melissan is dead, too?  You'd probably make a "
#| "promising Lord of Murder, you know..."
msgid ""
"I thought you were going to kill yourself after I was dead. Sure you won't "
"see some more evil once Melissan is dead, too? You'd probably make a "
"promising Lord of Murder, you know..."
msgstr ""
"Ich dachte, Ihr würdet Euch selbst töten, wenn ich tot bin.  Sicherlich "
"wollt Ihr doch nicht, dass Ihr noch mehr Böses seht, wenn Melissan ebenfalls"
" tot ist?  Ihr würdet einen vielversprechenden Herrn des Mordes abgeben, "
"glaubt mir..."

#: balth.tra:1103
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "Forget it.  This is pointless.  Let's just get this over with."
msgid "Forget it. This is pointless. Let's just get this over with."
msgstr "Vergesst es.  Das ist zwecklos.  Lasst uns einfach zum Ende kommen."

#: balth.tra:1104
msgid "Fight her together?"
msgstr "Sie gemeinsam bekämpfen?"

#: balth.tra:1105
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "No.  How could I trust you?  What if we were to vanquish Melissan, I would "
#| "be weakened... you could end my life there and everything I have been "
#| "working towards will be for nothing."
msgid ""
"No. How could I trust you? What if we were to vanquish Melissan, I would be "
"weakened... you could end my life there and everything I have been working "
"towards will be for nothing."
msgstr ""
"Nein.  Wie könnte ich Euch vertrauen?  Wenn wir Melissan besiegen würden, "
"wäre ich geschwächt... Ihr könntet mein Leben dort beenden, und alles, wofür"
" ich gearbeitet habe, würde umsonst gewesen sein."

#: balth.tra:1106
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "I had thought when this moment arrived, I would hold clearly to my purpose."
#| "  We must... end this, <CHARNAME>.  I wish this to be over with, one way or "
#| "the other."
msgid ""
"I had thought when this moment arrived, I would hold clearly to my purpose. "
"We must... end this, <CHARNAME>. I wish this to be over with, one way or the"
" other."
msgstr ""
"Ich hatte gedacht, wenn dieser Moment kommen würde, würde ich klar meine "
"Sache verfolgen.  Wir müssen... das hier beenden, <CHARNAME>.  Ich möchte "
"damit fertig sein, auf dem einen oder dem anderen Weg."

#: balth.tra:1107
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "Alright, Balthazar.  If that's what you want... let's end this now."
msgid "Alright, Balthazar. If that's what you want... let's end this now."
msgstr ""
"Nun gut, Balthasar.  Wenn es das ist, was Ihr wollt... dann lasst es uns "
"jetzt beenden."

#: balth.tra:1108
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "I am at a loss, <CHARNAME>.  You question me, and I have no good answers for"
#| " you.  My heart tells me that you must be killed, but I am not sure if I "
#| "should listen to it.  What... what would you have me do?"
msgid ""
"I am at a loss, <CHARNAME>. You question me, and I have no good answers for "
"you. My heart tells me that you must be killed, but I am not sure if I "
"should listen to it. What... what would you have me do?"
msgstr ""
"Ich bin ratlos, <CHARNAME>.  Ihr fragt mich, und ich habe keine guten "
"Antworten für Euch.  Mein Herz sagt mir, dass Ihr getötet werden müsst, aber"
" ich bin nicht sicher, ob ich darauf hören sollte.  Was... was wollt Ihr, "
"dass ich tue?"

#: balth.tra:1109
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "Join me, Balthazar.  Let us fight Melissan together, instead of doing what "
#| "she wants us to."
msgid ""
"Join me, Balthazar. Let us fight Melissan together, instead of doing what "
"she wants us to."
msgstr ""
"Schließt Euch mir an, Balthasar.  Lasst uns Melissan gemeinsam bekämpfen, "
"anstatt zu tun, was sie von uns will."

#: balth.tra:1110
#, fuzzy
#| msgid "I don't know, Balthazar.  But I don't want to fight you."
msgid "I don't know, Balthazar. But I don't want to fight you."
msgstr ""
"Ich weiß es nicht, Balthasar.  Aber ich will nicht gegen Euch kämpfen."

#: balth.tra:1111
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "Let us fight, then, if it must be.  Let me give you some peace at last."
msgid "Let us fight, then, if it must be. Let me give you some peace at last."
msgstr ""
"Dann lasst uns kämpfen, wenn es sein muss.  Ein wenig Frieden zumindest will"
" ich Euch geben."

#: balth.tra:1112
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "You're a weaker fool then I thought.  Let's just end this now, shall we?  I "
#| "have an appointment with god-hood."
msgid ""
"You're a bigger fool than I thought. Let's just end this now, shall we? I "
"have an appointment with god-hood."
msgstr ""
"Ihr seid ein Narr und schwächer, als ich glaubte.  Lasst uns das hier jetzt "
"beenden.  Ich habe eine Verabredung mit den Göttern."

#: balth.tra:1113
msgid "Yes... you are right."
msgstr "Ja... Ihr habt recht."

#: balth.tra:1114
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "Very well, then, <CHARNAME>.  I will join you.  You are a worthy "
#| "<PRO_MANWOMAN>.  Perhaps even worthy of turning Bhaal's dark taint and "
#| "making something better of it.  I do not know.  But I will take that chance."
msgid ""
"Very well, then, <CHARNAME>. I will join you. You are a worthy "
"<PRO_MANWOMAN>. Perhaps even worthy of turning Bhaal's dark taint and making"
" something better of it. I do not know. But I will take that chance."
msgstr ""
"Sehr gut,  <CHARNAME>.  Ich werde mich Euch anschließen.  Ihr seid ein "
"würdig<PRO_MANWOMAN>.  Vielleicht sogar würdig, Bhaals dunklen Makel zu "
"wenden und etwas Besseres daraus zu machen.  Ich weiß es nicht.  Aber ich "
"werde diese Chance nutzen."

#: balth.tra:1115
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "Let Melissan tremble when she sees us together, and we shall strike her down"
#| " as she deserves.  Even if Bhaal himself is resurrected, he will not be able"
#| " to hold out against us both.  I have preparations to make, <CHARNAME>.  Go "
#| "to the Throne of Bhaal.  When the time comes, I will be there."
msgid ""
"Let Melissan tremble when she sees us together, and we shall strike her down"
" as she deserves. Even if Bhaal himself is resurrected, he will not be able "
"to hold out against us both. I have preparations to make, <CHARNAME>. Go to "
"the Throne of Bhaal. When the time comes, I will be there."
msgstr ""
"Lasst Melissan zittern, wenn sie uns gemeinsam sieht, und wir werden sie "
"niederschmettern, wie sie es verdient.  Und wenn Bhaal selbst wiedererweckt "
"würde, er würde uns beide nicht bezwingen können.  Ich muss Vorbereitungen "
"treffen, <CHARNAME>.  Geht zum Thron des Bhaal.  Wenn die Zeit gekommen ist,"
" werde ich dort sein."

#: balth.tra:1116
msgid "I cannot, <CHARNAME>."
msgstr "Ich kann es nicht, <CHARNAME>."

#: balth.tra:1117
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "You must take the battle to Melissan.  It is your destiny to see that "
#| "Bhaal's legacy ends here and now.  But you must promise me, <CHARNAME>...you"
#| " must promise me that you will not give into the temptation.  Should you "
#| "defeat Melissan and the power become available to you, you must turn away "
#| "from it... you have seen your struggle as it is now, with only a sliver of "
#| "that taint.  Do not take it, <CHARNAME>...even a god can be tempted, you "
#| "must realize that.  Promise me you will turn it away."
msgid ""
"You must take the battle to Melissan. It is your destiny to see that Bhaal's"
" legacy ends here and now. But you must promise me, <CHARNAME>...you must "
"promise me that you will not give into the temptation. Should you defeat "
"Melissan and the power become available to you, you must turn away from "
"it... you have seen your struggle as it is now, with only a sliver of that "
"taint. Do not take it, <CHARNAME>...even a god can be tempted, you must "
"realize that. Promise me you will turn it away."
msgstr ""
"Ihr müsst Euch Melissan entgegenstellen.  Euer Schicksal ist es, darauf zu "
"achten, dass Bhaals Erbe hier und jetzt endet.  Aber Ihr müsst mir "
"versprechen, <CHARNAME>... Ihr müsst mir versprechen, dass Ihr der "
"Versuchung nicht erliegen werdet.  Solltet Ihr Melissan besiegen und über "
"die Macht verfügen, müsst Ihr Euch von ihr abwenden... Ihr habt gesehen, "
"welchen Kampf Ihr ausfechten müsst, gegen nur einen Splitter dieses Makels."
"  Nehmt ihn nicht, <CHARNAME>... selbst ein Gott kann in Versuchung geraten,"
" das müsst Ihr erkennen.  Versprecht mir, dass Ihr ihn zurückweist."

#: balth.tra:1118
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "If I am given the option, Balthazar... I will refuse the taint.  I swear it."
msgid ""
"If I am given the option, Balthazar... I will refuse the taint. I swear it."
msgstr ""
"Wenn ich vor die Wahl gestellt werde, Balthasar... werde ich den Makel "
"zurückweisen.  Ich schwöre es."

#: balth.tra:1119
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "No.  I will swear nothing of the kind.  Great good could come out of that "
#| "power, you don't know otherwise any better than I."
msgid ""
"No. I will swear nothing of the kind. Great good could come out of that "
"power, you don't know otherwise any better than I."
msgstr ""
"Nein.  Ich werde nichts dergleichen schwören.  Viel Gutes könnte aus dieser "
"Macht erwachsen, und Ihr wisst nicht mehr darüber als ich."

#: balth.tra:1120
#, fuzzy
#| msgid "Forget it!  I'll do no such thing!"
msgid "Forget it! I'll do no such thing!"
msgstr "Vergesst es!  So etwas werde ich nicht tun!"

#: balth.tra:1121
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "Then I am satisfied.  The essence of our sire ends with me... and with you."
#| "  May the gods forgive me.  May you... may you forgive me, "
#| "<PRO_BROTHERSISTER>..."
msgid ""
"Then I am satisfied. The essence of our sire ends with me... and with you. "
"May the gods forgive me. May you... may you forgive me, "
"<PRO_BROTHERSISTER>..."
msgstr ""
"Dann bin ich zufrieden.  Die Essenz unseres Erzeugers endet mit mir... und "
"mit Euch.  Mögen die Götter mir vergeben.  Mögt Ihr... mögt Ihr mir "
"vergeben, <PRO_BROTHERSISTER>..."

#: balth.tra:1122
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "Then we must do battle.  I... I am sorry, <PRO_BROTHERSISTER>.  I had hoped "
#| "this would be otherwise."
msgid ""
"Then we must do battle. I... I am sorry, <PRO_BROTHERSISTER>. I had hoped "
"this would be otherwise."
msgstr ""
"Dann müssen wir kämpfen.  Es... es tut mir leid, <PRO_BROTHERSISTER>.  Ich "
"hatte gehofft, es wäre anders gekommen."

#: balth.tra:1123
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "And I cannot trust that you will turn aside the power when it is offered to "
#| "you.  You have experienced the struggle even a sliver of Bhaal's taint has "
#| "brought you, yet I cannot believe that you would turn it aside.  I... I am "
#| "sorry, <PRO_BROTHERSISTER>...but I have no choice."
msgid ""
"And I cannot trust that you will turn aside the power when it is offered to "
"you. You have experienced the struggle even a sliver of Bhaal's taint has "
"brought you, yet I cannot believe that you would turn it aside. I... I am "
"sorry, <PRO_BROTHERSISTER>...but I have no choice."
msgstr ""
"Und ich kann nicht darauf vertrauen, dass Ihr die Macht zurückweist, wenn "
"sie Euch angeboten wird.  Ihr habt den Kampf erlebt, den nur ein Splitter "
"von Bhaals Makel Euch gebracht hat, doch ich kann nicht glauben, dass Ihr "
"ihn zurückweisen würdet.  Es... es tut mir leid, <PRO_BROTHERSISTER>... aber"
" ich habe keine Wahl."

#: balth.tra:1124
#, fuzzy
#| msgid "So be it.  Come, my pupils... may the gods help us all."
msgid "So be it. Come, my pupils... may the gods help us all."
msgstr ""
"So sei es.  Kommt, meine Schüler... mögen die Götter uns allen beistehen."

#: balth.tra:1125
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "No.  Further dialogue is pointless.  Let us end this now, <CHARNAME>...and "
#| "may the gods have pity on us all."
msgid ""
"No. Further dialogue is pointless. Let us end this now, <CHARNAME>...and may"
" the gods have pity on us all."
msgstr ""
"Nein.  Weitere Gespräche sind zwecklos.  Lasst uns das hier beenden, "
"<CHARNAME>... und mögen die Götter sich unser erbarmen."

#: balth.tra:1126
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "Perhaps what you are saying holds merit.  But what if I died during the "
#| "battle?  What if I was weakened, in the end... you might find yourself... "
#| "tempted.  How could I trust you?"
msgid ""
"Perhaps what you are saying holds merit. But what if I died during the "
"battle? What if I was weakened, in the end... you might find yourself... "
"tempted. How could I trust you?"
msgstr ""
"Vielleicht ist ja Wahrheit in dem, was Ihr sagt.  Aber was, wenn ich in der "
"Schlacht falle?  Was, wenn ich geschwächt werde, und am Ende... würdet "
"Ihr... in Versuchung geraten.  Wie könnte ich Euch vertrauen?"

#: balth.tra:1128
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "I don't know how to explain it, exactly, but she must have used you!  She "
#| "used everyone else!  I didn't trust her and she even got me to do what she "
#| "wanted!"
msgid ""
"I don't know how to explain it, exactly, but she must have used you! She "
"used everyone else! I didn't trust her and she even got me to do what she "
"wanted!"
msgstr ""
"Ich weiß nicht, wie ich es erklären soll, aber sie muss Euch benutzt haben!"
"  Sie hat auch alle anderen benutzt!  Ich habe ihr nicht vertraut, und sogar"
" mich hat sie dazu gebracht zu tun, was sie wollte!"

#: balth.tra:1129
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "Think about it, Balthazar!  You honestly think she didn't know what your "
#| "plans were?  Do you think you took her by surprise?  Even I saw it coming, "
#| "and there was nothing I could do to stop it!"
msgid ""
"Think about it, Balthazar! You honestly think she didn't know what your "
"plans were? Do you think you took her by surprise? Even I saw it coming, and"
" there was nothing I could do to stop it!"
msgstr ""
"Denkt darüber nach, Balthasar!  Ihr denkt wirklich, sie hätte nicht gewusst,"
" was Eure Pläne waren?  Glaubt Ihr, Ihr hättet sie überrascht?  Sogar ich "
"habe es kommen sehen, und es gab nichts, was ich hätte tun können, um es zu "
"verhindern!"

#: balth.tra:1130
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "She used you to get rid of the other Bhaalspawn, obviously.  Think about it!"
#| "  She knew what you were planning all along.  She wanted all the Bhaalspawn "
#| "dead... and she wants us to fight!  She *wants* this to happen!!"
msgid ""
"She used you to get rid of the other Bhaalspawn, obviously. Think about it! "
"She knew what you were planning all along. She wanted all the Bhaalspawn "
"dead... and she wants us to fight! She *wants* this to happen!"
msgstr ""
"Sie hat Euch offensichtlich benutzt, um all die andere Bhaalbrut "
"loszuwerden.  Denkt darüber nach!  Sie wusste die ganze Zeit, was Ihr "
"geplant habt.  Sie wollte, dass die gesamte Bhaalbrut tot ist... uns sie "
"will, dass wir gegeneinander kämpfen!  Sie *will*, dass dies geschieht!"

#: balth.tra:1131
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "Of course she used me, <CHARNAME>.  And no doubt she knew my plans as well "
#| "as I knew hers.  This changes nothing."
msgid ""
"Of course she used me, <CHARNAME>. And no doubt she knew my plans as well as"
" I knew hers. This changes nothing."
msgstr ""
"Natürlich hat sie mich benutzt, <CHARNAME>.  Und zweifellos kannte sie meine"
" Pläne, wie auch ich die ihren kannte.  Das ändert nichts."

#: balth.tra:1132
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "You... may be right, <CHARNAME>.  But that does not mean that my plan will "
#| "fail.  Melissan underestimates me, I am sure of that... just as she "
#| "underestimates you."
msgid ""
"You... may be right, <CHARNAME>. But that does not mean that my plan will "
"fail. Melissan underestimates me, I am sure of that... just as she "
"underestimates you."
msgstr ""
"Ihr... könntet recht haben, <CHARNAME>.  Aber das bedeutet nicht, dass mein "
"Plan erfolglos sein wird.  Melissan unterschätzt mich, ich bin mir da "
"sicher... genauso, wie sie auch Euch unterschätzt."

#: balth.tra:1133
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "I... perhaps you are right, <CHARNAME>.  I see the wisdom of your words.  "
#| "Still... this does not mean my plan is doomed to failure.  Or is it?"
msgid ""
"I... perhaps you are right, <CHARNAME>. I see the wisdom of your words. "
"Still... this does not mean my plan is doomed to failure. Or is it?"
msgstr ""
"Ich... vielleicht habt Ihr recht, <CHARNAME>.  Ich sehe Weisheit in Euren "
"Worten. Dennoch... das bedeutet nicht, dass mein Plan zum Scheitern "
"verurteilt ist.  Oder doch?"

#: balth.tra:1134
#, fuzzy
#| msgid "I must resist it.  I will.  I have no choice."
msgid "I must resist it. I will. I have no choice."
msgstr "Ich muss ihm widerstehen.  Ich werde es.  Ich habe keine Wahl."

#: balth.tra:1135
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "But... you have shown great willpower, as well.  Despite the taint in your "
#| "soul, you have struggled against it just as I have.  What makes me more "
#| "worthy...?  No, I must not question myself!  Not now!"
msgid ""
"But... you have shown great willpower, as well. Despite the taint in your "
"soul, you have struggled against it just as I have. What makes me more "
"worthy...? No, I must not question myself! Not now!"
msgstr ""
"Aber... Ihr habt ebenfalls große Willenskraft bewiesen.  Trotz des Makels in"
" Eurer Seele habt Ihr dagegen angekämpft, genau wie ich.  Weshalb sollte ich"
" also würdiger sein...?  Nein, ich darf nicht an mir zweifeln!  Nicht jetzt!"

#: balth.tra:1136
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "You are certainly no better a candidate for resisting such temptation, "
#| "<CHARNAME>.  I would trust myself far more than I would trust you.  To send "
#| "you to the Throne would be to give up everything I have believed in."
msgid ""
"You are certainly no better a candidate for resisting such temptation, "
"<CHARNAME>. I would trust myself far more than I would trust you. To send "
"you to the Throne would be to give up everything I have believed in."
msgstr ""
"Ihr seid sicherlich kein besserer Kandidat, dieser Versuchung zu "
"widerstehen, <CHARNAME>.  Ich würde mir selbst weit mehr trauen als Euch.  "
"Euch zum Thron zu senden, würde bedeuten, alles aufzugeben, woran ich "
"geglaubt habe."

#: balth.tra:1137
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "Strength is nothing, <CHARNAME>.  You may vanquish me with your might, and "
#| "you may even vanquish Melissan.  But you will never vanquish yourself.  "
#| "Might will bring you no peace... this I know.  And this is why I must be the"
#| " last."
msgid ""
"Strength is nothing, <CHARNAME>. You may vanquish me with your might, and "
"you may even vanquish Melissan. But you will never vanquish yourself. Might "
"will bring you no peace... this I know. And this is why I must be the last."
msgstr ""
"Stärke ist bedeutungslos, <CHARNAME>.  Ihr könntet mich überwinden mit Eurer"
" Macht, und Ihr könntet sogar Melissan überwinden.  Aber Ihr könnt nie Euch "
"selbst überwinden.  Macht wird Euch keinen Frieden bringen... das weiß ich."
"  Und deshalb muss ich der Letzte sein."

#: balth.tra:1138
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "I am tired of the battles I have fought, <CHARNAME>.  I am tired of the "
#| "anguish that I have endured, placing the greater good above the welfare of "
#| "others, of myself and my own immortal soul.  It will be enough that Bhaal's "
#| "legacy is destroyed, there is no temptation beyond that."
msgid ""
"I am tired of the battles I have fought, <CHARNAME>. I am tired of the "
"anguish that I have endured, placing the greater good above the welfare of "
"others, of myself and my own immortal soul. It will be enough that Bhaal's "
"legacy is destroyed, there is no temptation beyond that."
msgstr ""
"Ich bin der Schlachten müde, die ich geschlagen habe, <CHARNAME>.  Ich habe "
"die Qualen satt, die ich ertragen habe, indem ich ein größeres Gutes über "
"das Wohlergehen von anderen, meiner selbst und meiner unsterblichen Seele "
"gestellt habe.  Es wird ausreichen, dass Bhaals Hinterlassenschaft zerstört "
"ist, ich habe keine Ziele darüber hinaus."

#: balth.tra:1139
#, fuzzy
#| msgid "But I do.  It is my destiny.  What other choice have I?"
msgid "But I do. It is my destiny. What other choice have I?"
msgstr ""
"Aber ich muss es.  Es ist mein Schicksal.  Welche andere Wahl sollte ich "
"haben?"

#: balth.tra:1140
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "You always have a choice, Balthazar.  Don't be a slave to Alaundo's "
#| "prophecy!  I have fought against it ever since I found out about my heritage"
#| " and I will *not* give up!"
msgid ""
"You always have a choice, Balthazar. Don't be a slave to Alaundo's prophecy!"
" I have fought against it ever since I found out about my heritage and I "
"will *not* give up!"
msgstr ""
"Ihr habt immer eine Wahl, Balthasar.  Seid kein Sklave der Prophezeiung "
"Alaundos!  Ich habe dagegen gekämpft, seit ich mein Erbe kenne, und ich "
"werde *nicht* aufgeben!"

#: balth.tra:1141
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "Alaundo's prophecy does not mean the Bhaalspawn must be destroyers, "
#| "Balthazar!  It also means we can stop the prophecy from becoming true, I "
#| "know this!"
msgid ""
"Alaundo's prophecy does not mean the Bhaalspawn must be destroyers, "
"Balthazar! It also means we can stop the prophecy from becoming true, I know"
" this!"
msgstr ""
"Alaundos Prophezeiung bedeutet nicht, dass die Bhaalbrut Zerstörer sein "
"muss, Balthasar! Sie bedeutet auch, dass wir es verhindern können, dass die "
"Prophezeiung eintrifft! Ich weiß das!"

#: balth.tra:1142
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "You can walk away.  You can do what's right, Balthazar, what you know to be "
#| "right instead of what you've resigned yourself to."
msgid ""
"You can walk away. You can do what's right, Balthazar, what you know to be "
"right instead of what you've resigned yourself to."
msgstr ""
"Ihr könnt weggehen.  Ihr könnt tun, was richtig ist, Balthasar, Ihr könnt "
"das tun, was Ihr als richtig erkannt habt, und nicht das, womit Ihr Euch "
"abgefunden habt."

#: balth.tra:1143
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "You are walking a path that you don't need to, Balthazar.  You see yourself "
#| "as evil, but it doesn't have to be that way."
msgid ""
"You are walking a path that you don't need to, Balthazar. You see yourself "
"as evil, but it doesn't have to be that way."
msgstr ""
"Ihr geht einen Weg, den Ihr nicht gehen müsst, Balthasar.  Ihr seht Euch "
"selbst als böse, aber das muss nicht so sein.."

#: balth.tra:1144
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "I am your <PRO_BROTHERSISTER>, Balthazar.  Let us fight what is inevitable!"
#| "  We can work together!"
msgid ""
"I am your <PRO_BROTHERSISTER>, Balthazar. Let us fight what is inevitable! "
"We can work together!"
msgstr ""
"Ich bin Euer Bruder, Balthasar.  Lasst uns das Unvermeidbare bekämpfen!  Wir"
" können zusammenarbeiten!"

#: balth.tra:1145
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "Forget it.  There's no point in discussing this with you, is there?  Let's "
#| "get this over with."
msgid ""
"Forget it. There's no point in discussing this with you, is there? Let's get"
" this over with."
msgstr ""
"Vergesst es.  Es ist zwecklos, das mit Euch zu diskutieren.  Lasst uns damit"
" zum Ende kommen."

#: balth.tra:1146
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "You are impressive with your words, <CHARNAME>.  I can feel destiny altering"
#| " to your will, how you are the center of it all... how is it that I did not "
#| "see this before?"
msgid ""
"You are impressive with your words, <CHARNAME>. I can feel destiny altering "
"to your will, how you are the center of it all... how is it that I did not "
"see this before?"
msgstr ""
"Eure Worte sind beeindruckend, <CHARNAME>.  Ich kann spüren, dass sich das "
"Schicksal nach Eurem Willen ändert, dass Ihr das Zentrum all dessen seid... "
"wie kommt es, dass ich das nicht eher gesehen habe?"

#: balth.tra:1147
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "But the simple truth is your words ring hollow to me.  I do not believe "
#| "them.  You have fought against destiny, yet I see it in you even the more as"
#| " you speak."
msgid ""
"But the simple truth is your words ring hollow to me. I do not believe them."
" You have fought against destiny, yet I see it in you even the more as you "
"speak."
msgstr ""
"Aber die einfache Wahrheit ist, dass Eure Worte hohl klingen.  Ich glaube "
"nicht an sie.  Ihr hab gegen das Schicksal gekämpft, dennoch kann ich es in "
"Euch erkennen, je länger Ihr sprecht."

#: balth.tra:1148
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "Perhaps... perhaps there is something to your words.  I look within myself "
#| "and see how rigidly I have held myself to my destiny... and I feel hollow.  "
#| "But I... cannot believe that this has been for nothing."
msgid ""
"Perhaps... perhaps there is something to your words. I look within myself "
"and see how rigidly I have held myself to my destiny... and I feel hollow. "
"But I... cannot believe that this has been for nothing."
msgstr ""
"Vielleicht... vielleicht ist an Euren Worten etwas dran.  Ich blicke in mich"
" hinein und sehe, wie starr ich an meinem Schicksal festgehalten habe... und"
" ich fühle mich hohl.  Aber ich... kann nicht glauben, dass all dies umsonst"
" gewesen sei."

#: balth.tra:1149
#, fuzzy
#| msgid "What do you mean?  How do you know this?"
msgid "What do you mean? How do you know this?"
msgstr "Was meint Ihr damit?  Woher wisst Ihr das?"

#: balth.tra:1150
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "It was told to me by a Solar, an agent of prophecy!  It... oh, I know how it"
#| " sounds, but it's true!"
msgid ""
"It was told to me by a Solar, an agent of prophecy! It... oh, I know how it "
"sounds, but it's true!"
msgstr ""
"Es wurde mir von einem Solar gesagt, einem Diener der Prophezeiung!  Es... "
"oh, ich weiß, wie das klingt, aber es stimmt!"

#: balth.tra:1151
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "I have been told many things by agents of Alaundo's prophecy... higher "
#| "beings that have sought me out to prepare me.  Alaundo's prophecy does not "
#| "necessarily mean what you think it does, Balthazar."
msgid ""
"I have been told many things by agents of Alaundo's prophecy... higher "
"beings that have sought me out to prepare me. Alaundo's prophecy does not "
"necessarily mean what you think it does, Balthazar."
msgstr ""
"Vieles wurde mir gesagt von den Dienern der Prophezeiung Alaundos... höheren"
" Wesen, die zu mir kamen, um mich vorzubereiten.  Alaundos Prophezeiung "
"bedeutet nicht unbedingt das, was Ihr denkt, Balthasar."

#: balth.tra:1152
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "A Solar has been my mentor since this began, guiding me and preparing me for"
#| " what is to come.  The prophecy is not so simple as you think it to be, no "
#| "matter how we assume it to be.  Think about it and you'll know it to be "
#| "true, Balthazar... everything has more than one side."
msgid ""
"A Solar has been my mentor since this began, guiding me and preparing me for"
" what is to come. The prophecy is not so simple as you think it to be, no "
"matter how we assume it to be. Think about it and you'll know it to be true,"
" Balthazar... everything has more than one side."
msgstr ""
"Ein Solar war mein Mentor, seit dies alles begann, er leitete mich und "
"bereitete mich vor auf das, was kommen wird.  Die Prophezeiung ist nicht so "
"einfach, wie wir glauben. Denkt darüber nach und erkennt, dass das wahr ist,"
" Balthasar... alles hat mehr als eine Seite."

#: balth.tra:1153
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "I have no agent of the heavens to interpret my destiny for me, <CHARNAME>.  "
#| "And my path remains clear."
msgid ""
"I have no agent of the heavens to interpret my destiny for me, <CHARNAME>. "
"And my path remains clear."
msgstr ""
"Ich habe keinen Diener der Himmel, das Schicksal für mich zu deuten, "
"<CHARNAME>.  Und mein Weg bleibt unverändert."

#: balth.tra:1154
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "You plant a seed of doubt in me, <CHARNAME>, and I begin to wonder.  Yet... "
#| "it seems that my destiny may differ from yours.  I have no heavenly "
#| "guidance.  Perhaps my path has been made for me, yet."
msgid ""
"You plant a seed of doubt in me, <CHARNAME>, and I begin to wonder. Yet... "
"it seems that my destiny may differ from yours. I have no heavenly guidance."
" Perhaps my path has been made for me, yet."
msgstr ""
"Ihr sät den Samen des Zweifels in mir, <CHARNAME>, und ich beginne zu "
"staunen.  Doch... es scheint, als sei mein Schicksal verschieden von Eurem."
"  Ich habe keine himmlische Führung.  Vielleicht ist mein Weg schon gebahnt."

#: balth.tra:1155
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "What you say is incredible, and yet... it does make sense.  Have I prepared "
#| "myself for all this time in error?  How could this be?"
msgid ""
"What you say is incredible, and yet... it does make sense. Have I prepared "
"myself for all this time in error? How could this be?"
msgstr ""
"Was Ihr sagt, ist unglaublich, und doch... macht es Sinn.  Habe ich mich die"
" ganze Zeit falsch vorbereitet?  Wie kann das sein?"

#: balth.tra:1156
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "An appealing notion, to walk away.  Would that I could do so.  Would that "
#| "any of us could have done so."
msgid ""
"An appealing notion, to walk away. Would that I could do so. Would that any "
"of us could have done so."
msgstr ""
"Ein verlockender Gedanke, wegzugehen.  Ich wollte, ich könnte es tun.  Ich "
"wollte, jeder von uns hätte es tun können."

#: balth.tra:1157
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "But perhaps I have resigned myself to a path that is not what it seems.  You"
#| " are... hardly what I expected for the last of the Bhaalspawn, <CHARNAME>.  "
#| "Perhaps there is hope... or perhaps I am only deluding myself."
msgid ""
"But perhaps I have resigned myself to a path that is not what it seems. You "
"are... hardly what I expected for the last of the Bhaalspawn, <CHARNAME>. "
"Perhaps there is hope... or perhaps I am only deluding myself."
msgstr ""
"Aber vielleicht habe ich mich mit einem Weg abgefunden, der nicht so ist, "
"wie er zu sein scheint.  Ihr seid... nicht das, was ich mir unter dem "
"Letzten der Bhaalbrut vorgestellt habe, <CHARNAME>.  Vielleicht gibt es "
"Hoffnung... oder vielleicht täusche ich mich nur selbst."

#: balth.tra:1158
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "But that is a fool's notion, <CHARNAME>, and I am no fool.  There is no such"
#| " option available to me or any of us, no matter how appealing you may make "
#| "it seem."
msgid ""
"But that is a fool's notion, <CHARNAME>, and I am no fool. There is no such "
"option available to me or any of us, no matter how appealing you may make it"
" seem."
msgstr ""
"Aber das ist der Gedanke eines Narren, <CHARNAME>, und ich bin kein Narr.  "
"Es gibt diese Möglichkeit weder für mich noch für einen anderen von uns, so "
"verlockend Ihr sie auch darstellt."

#: balth.tra:1159
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "No!  You have listened to nothing I have said!  It *is* that way because "
#| "there is no choice for us!  You would have me forget all the murders I have "
#| "committed with my own hands, all the wrongs I have done in the name of the "
#| "greater good... I cannot forget!  I will not forgive myself and I will *not*"
#| " allow others to be afflicted with the taint I possess!"
msgid ""
"No! You have listened to nothing I have said! It *is* that way because there"
" is no choice for us! You would have me forget all the murders I have "
"committed with my own hands, all the wrongs I have done in the name of the "
"greater good... I cannot forget! I will not forgive myself and I will *not* "
"allow others to be afflicted with the taint I possess!"
msgstr ""
"Nein! Ihr habt nichts von dem verstanden, was ich gesagt habe!  Es *ist* "
"dieser Weg, weil es für uns keine Wahl gibt!  Ihr wollt, dass ich all die "
"Morde vergesse, die ich mit eigener Hand begangen habe, all das Übel, das "
"ich verursacht habe im Namen eines größeren Guten... ich kann nicht "
"vergessen!  Ich werde mir nicht vergeben, und ich werde *nicht* zulassen, "
"dass andere vom gleichen Makel wie ich selbst befallen werden!"

#: balth.tra:1160
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "You have considerable charisma, <CHARNAME>...but it is because we are "
#| "siblings that we cannot work together.  You know as well as I what the "
#| "essence seeks, and it will not be satisfied until our destiny is culminated."
msgid ""
"You have considerable charisma, <CHARNAME>...but it is because we are "
"siblings that we cannot work together. You know as well as I what the "
"essence seeks, and it will not be satisfied until our destiny is culminated."
msgstr ""
"Ihr seid eine sehr charismatische Person, <CHARNAME>... aber weil wir "
"Geschwister sind, können wir nicht zusammenarbeiten.  Ihr wisst genauso gut "
"wie ich, was die Essenz will, und sie wird nicht zufrieden sein, bis unser "
"Schicksal seinen Höhepunkt erreicht hat."

#: balth.tra:1161
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "I make no judgement upon you, <CHARNAME>.  You are what you were born to be."
#| "  I can only trust myself to hold to the path of good that will lead to the "
#| "destruction of the true evil that threatens FaerÃ»n.  There is no other path"
#| " for me."
msgid ""
"I make no judgement upon you, <CHARNAME>. You are what you were born to be. "
"I can only trust myself to hold to the path of good that will lead to the "
"destruction of the true evil that threatens Faerun. There is no other path "
"for me."
msgstr ""
"Ich richte Euch nicht, <CHARNAME>.  Ihr seid der, als der Ihr geboren "
"wurdet. Ich kann nur mir selbst vertrauen, dass ich auf dem Weg bleibe, der "
"zur Vernichtung des wahren Bösen führt, das Faerûn bedroht.  Es gibt keinen "
"anderen Weg für mich."

#: balth.tra:1162
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "Look at the suffering you have brought to Amkethran!  Your monks terrorize "
#| "the innocent at your command!  You hire soulless mercenaries that cut down "
#| "the innocent at the slightest provocation!  And all for nothing!  You call "
#| "these the actions of a good man?"
msgid ""
"Look at the suffering you have brought to Amkethran! Your monks terrorize "
"the innocent at your command! You hire soulless mercenaries that cut down "
"the innocent at the slightest provocation! And all for nothing! You call "
"these the actions of a good man?"
msgstr ""
"Schaut auf das Leid, das Ihr über Amkethran gebracht habt!  Eure Mönche "
"terrorisieren die Unschuldigen auf Euren Befehl!  Ihr heuert gewissenlose "
"Söldner an, die beim geringsten Anlass die Unschuldigen niedersäbeln!  Und "
"all das für nichts!  Das nennt Ihr die Taten eines guten Mannes?"

#: balth.tra:1163
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "A truly good man would have stood against Melissan from the beginning.  You "
#| "say you wanted to find out who the Five were... and yet I defeated them "
#| "without your scheming.  It was your choice to join the Five in their reign "
#| "of destruction, so live up to it!"
msgid ""
"A truly good man would have stood against Melissan from the beginning. You "
"say you wanted to find out who the Five were... and yet I defeated them "
"without your scheming. It was your choice to join the Five in their reign of"
" destruction, so live up to it!"
msgstr ""
"Ein wahrhaft guter Mensch würde sich von Beginn an gegen Melissan gestellt "
"haben.  Ihr sagtet, Ihr wolltet herausfinden, wer die Fünf waren... und doch"
" habe ich sie ohne Eure Intrigen besiegt.  Es war Eure Entscheidung, die "
"Fünf in ihrer zerstörerischen Herrschaft zu unterstützen, also handelt "
"danach!"

#: balth.tra:1164
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "You make no judgement upon me?  Don't make me laugh!  Inevitability is only "
#| "the newest excuse for yet one more murder!  You would make our father proud!"
msgid ""
"You make no judgement upon me? Don't make me laugh! Inevitability is only "
"the newest excuse for yet one more murder! You would make our father proud!"
msgstr ""
"Ihr richtet nicht über mich?  Bringt mich nicht zum Lachen!  "
"Unvermeidlichkeit ist nur eine weitere Entschuldigung für noch einen Mord!  "
"Ihr würdet unserem Vater Freude machen!"

#: balth.tra:1165
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "And what if that is my path, too, Balthazar?  You say you don't judge me, "
#| "and yet you hold yourself to some duty as the only person who can fight "
#| "against evil?  Do you know destiny so well that you can say for certain "
#| "where it leads for someone else, never mind yourself?"
msgid ""
"And what if that is my path, too, Balthazar? You say you don't judge me, and"
" yet you hold yourself to some duty as the only person who can fight against"
" evil? Do you know destiny so well that you can say for certain where it "
"leads for someone else, never mind yourself?"
msgstr ""
"Und wenn das auch mein Weg ist, Balthasar?  Ihr sagt, Ihr richtet mich "
"nicht, und doch seht Ihr Euch verpflichtet, als wärt Ihr die einzige Person,"
" die gegen das Böse kämpfen könnte?  Kennt Ihr das Schicksal so gut, dass "
"Ihr mit Sicherheit sagen könnt, wohin es jemanden anderes leitet, ganz zu "
"schweigen von Euch selbst?"

#: balth.tra:1166
#, fuzzy
#| msgid "Then let's get this over with.  I'm tired of talking."
msgid "Then let's get this over with. I'm tired of talking."
msgstr "Dann lasst uns das hier beenden.  Ich bin der Gespräche müde."

#: balth.tra:1167
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "It... it is true.  I paid little attention to my men's actions, but I... I "
#| "knew what they were doing.  I thought it a great sacridice, necessary to "
#| "maintain secrecy, to attain my ultimate goal that they, in their ignorance, "
#| "did not know would benefit them more in the end.  But... it is how we treat "
#| "the most helpless of our brethren in the worst of times that marks the "
#| "goodness of a man, does it not?  I... I am ashamed, <CHARNAME>.  I sought..."
#| " only to do what was best for us all."
msgid ""
"It... it is true. I paid little attention to my men's actions, but I... I "
"knew what they were doing. I thought it a great sacridice, necessary to "
"maintain secrecy, to attain my ultimate goal that they, in their ignorance, "
"did not know would benefit them more in the end. But... it is how we treat "
"the most helpless of our brethren in the worst of times that marks the "
"goodness of a man, does it not? I... I am ashamed, <CHARNAME>. I sought... "
"only to do what was best for us all."
msgstr ""
"Es... es ist wahr.  Ich achtete wenig auf die Taten meiner Männer, doch "
"ich... ich wusste, was sie taten.  Ich hielt es für ein großes Opfer, "
"notwendig, um das Geheimnis zu wahren, um mein eigentliches Ziel zu "
"erreichen, von dem sie in ihrer Unwissenheit nicht begriffen, dass es ihnen "
"am Ende mehr nützen würde.  Aber... wie wir die hilflosesten unserer Brüder "
"in den schwierigsten Zeiten behandeln, ist das Zeichen für die Güte eines "
"Menschen, nicht wahr?  Ich... ich schäme mich, <CHARNAME>.  Ich strebte "
"danach... nach dem, was für uns alle das Beste wäre."

#: balth.tra:1168
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "You found out who the Five were through Melissan's scheming... and through, "
#| "in no small part, my own.  But who is to say that things might not have been"
#| " different?  Who are *you* to say that things might have been different?"
msgid ""
"You found out who the Five were through Melissan's scheming... and through, "
"in no small part, my own. But who is to say that things might not have been "
"different? Who are *you* to say that things might have been different?"
msgstr ""
"Ihr habt durch Melissans Intrigen herausgefunden, wer die Fünf waren... und "
"durch meine eigenen, in nicht geringem Maße.  Aber wer kann sagen, dass die "
"Dinge nicht hätten anders laufen können?  Wer seid *Ihr*, dass Ihr "
"behauptet, es hätte anders sein können?"

#: balth.tra:1169
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "But... it is true, nevertheless.  I have taken the easy path, and have done "
#| "much that has brought harm to others in the name of necessity.  But when "
#| "does 'necessity' cross into the realm of evil?  I... I am ashamed, "
#| "<CHARNAME>."
msgid ""
"But... it is true, nevertheless. I have taken the easy path, and have done "
"much that has brought harm to others in the name of necessity. But when does"
" 'necessity' cross into the realm of evil? I... I am ashamed, <CHARNAME>."
msgstr ""
"Aber... es ist dennoch wahr.  Ich bin den einfachen Weg gegangen und habe "
"viel getan, das anderen im Namen der Notwendigkeit Leid gebracht hat.  Aber "
"wann gleitet die \"Notwendigkeit\" hinüber ins Böse?  Ich... ich schäme "
"mich, <CHARNAME>."

#: balth.tra:1170
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "I do not stand here proud of my accomplishments in attaining what I see to "
#| "be a necessary goal... but neither should you.  You have blundered about, "
#| "causing more harm by your negligence than I ever could by my plotting."
msgid ""
"I do not stand here proud of my accomplishments in attaining what I see to "
"be a necessary goal... but neither should you. You have blundered about, "
"causing more harm by your negligence than I ever could by my plotting."
msgstr ""
"Ich stehe nicht hier, stolz auf das, was ich erreicht habe, indem ich ein "
"Ziel verfolgte, das ich als notwendig ansehe... aber Ihr solltet ebenso "
"wenig stolz sein.  Ihr seid herumgestolpert, habt durch Eure Nachlässigkeit "
"mehr Leid verursacht als ich es mit meinen Intrigen jemals könnte."

#: balth.tra:1171
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "I will *not* be mocked so!  I have sacrificed my entire life, the people of "
#| "this village, everything I have in order to see this evil destroyed!  "
#| "Destroyed, all of it!  I cry out to Ao the Overfather that such evil must "
#| "not be allowed to live in the hearts of mortals, and I *will* be heard!"
msgid ""
"I will *not* be mocked so! I have sacrificed my entire life, the people of "
"this village, everything I have in order to see this evil destroyed! "
"Destroyed, all of it! I cry out to Ao the Overfather that such evil must not"
" be allowed to live in the hearts of mortals, and I *will* be heard!"
msgstr ""
"Ich lasse mich *nicht* auf diese Weise verspotten!  Ich habe mein ganzes "
"Leben, die Bewohner dieses Dorfes, alles, was ich habe, geopfert, um dieses "
"Böse zu zerstören!  Vollständig zerstören!  Ich rufe zu Ao dem Übervater, "
"dass solches Böse nicht in den Herzen von Sterblichen leben darf, und ich "
"*werde* erhört werden!"

#: balth.tra:1172
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "I... know only what the temptations are that the taints puts upon us, "
#| "<CHARNAME>.  I know only that if our power was to grow, if your power was to"
#| " grow, that so would the temptation."
msgid ""
"I... know only what the temptations are that the taints puts upon us, "
"<CHARNAME>. I know only that if our power was to grow, if your power was to "
"grow, that so would the temptation."
msgstr ""
"Ich... kenne nur die Versuchungen, die der Makel uns auferlegt, <CHARNAME>."
"  Ich weiß nur, dass, wenn unsere Macht wächst, wenn Eure Macht wächst, auch"
" die Versuchungen wachsen werden."

#: balth.tra:1173
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "But... you have been successful in fighting temptation.  More successful "
#| "than I.  I have... done much that I regret, in the name of good.  My people "
#| "suffer because I held my ultimate goal above all else... but is it not true "
#| "that our treatment of the least of our brethren is the true judge of a man's"
#| " soul?  I... I am ashamed."
msgid ""
"But... you have been successful in fighting temptation. More successful than"
" I. I have... done much that I regret, in the name of good. My people suffer"
" because I held my ultimate goal above all else... but is it not true that "
"our treatment of the least of our brethren is the true judge of a man's "
"soul? I... I am ashamed."
msgstr ""
"Aber... Ihr wart erfolgreich, gegen die Versuchung zu kämpfen.  "
"Erfolgreicher als ich.  Ich habe... im Namen des Guten vieles getan, das ich"
" bedaure.  Mein Volk leidet, weil ich mein letztes Ziel über alles andere "
"stellte... Aber ist es nicht so, dass unser Verhalten gegenüber den "
"geringsten unserer Brüder der wahre Richter der menschlichen Seele ist?  "
"Ich... ich schäme mich."

#: balth.tra:1174
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "And despite what you might profess, I think the taint sits closer to your "
#| "heart then you would have me believe.  I must walk my own path, "
#| "<CHARNAME>...and you must walk yours."
msgid ""
"And despite what you might profess, I think the taint sits closer to your "
"heart then you would have me believe. I must walk my own path, "
"<CHARNAME>...and you must walk yours."
msgstr ""
"Und im Gegensatz zu dem, was Ihr behauptet, denke ich, dass der Makel näher "
"an Eurem Herzen sitzt, als Ihr mich glauben lassen wollt.  Ich muss meinen "
"eigenen Weg gehen, <CHARNAME>... und Ihr den Euren."

#: balth.tra:1175
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "Very well.  Come, my students... my teachings are ended.  We make our last "
#| "stand now for what is right.  May the gods have pity on us all."
msgid ""
"Very well. Come, my students... my teachings are ended. We make our last "
"stand now for what is right. May the gods have pity on us all."
msgstr ""
"Gut.  Kommt, meine Schüler... mein Unterricht ist beendet.  Wir stehen das "
"letzte Mal auf für das Gute.  Mögen die Götter sich unser erbarmen."

#: balth.tra:1176
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "Even had destiny not brought us to this point, I doubt things would have "
#| "been different.  Perhaps if you had not borne the taint of our sire, things "
#| "might have been different with you.  I would have liked to meet a "
#| "<PRO_MANWOMAN> such as yourself without the taint on your soul, I think.  "
#| "But now I have little choice."
msgid ""
"Even had destiny not brought us to this point, I doubt things would have "
"been different. Perhaps if you had not borne the taint of our sire, things "
"might have been different with you. I would have liked to meet a "
"<PRO_MANWOMAN> such as yourself without the taint on your soul, I think. But"
" now I have little choice."
msgstr ""
"Selbst wenn das Schicksal uns nicht hierher gebracht hätte, bezweifle ich, "
"dass die Dinge anders wären.  Vielleicht, wenn Ihr nicht den Makel unseres "
"Erzeugers tragen würdet, hätten die Dinge für Euch anders sein können.  Ich "
"hätte gern jemanden wie euch getroffen, ohne den Makel auf Eurer Seele.  "
"Aber nun habe ich keine Wahl."

#: balth.tra:1177
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "Would that your claim of innocence meant anything to the dead of Saradush.  "
#| "Were I to question the recent dead of Athkatla, of Baldur's Gate, of "
#| "Candlekeep... would I not find some who would claim such innocence for "
#| "themselves?  Who died merely because they were caught in your wake?"
msgid ""
"Would that your claim of innocence meant anything to the dead of Saradush. "
"Were I to question the recent dead of Athkatla, of Baldur's Gate, of "
"Candlekeep... would I not find some who would claim such innocence for "
"themselves? Who died merely because they were caught in your wake?"
msgstr ""
"Ich wünschte, dass Euer Beteuern der Unschuld für die Toten von Saradush "
"irgendeine Bedeutung hätte.  Würde ich die Toten der letzten Zeit aus "
"Atkatla, aus Baldurs Tor, aus Kerzenburg fragen... würde ich nicht jemanden "
"finden, der diese Unschuld auch für sich beansprucht?  Wer ist alles "
"gestorben, nur weil er gefangen war in Eurem Schlepptau?"

#: balth.tra:1178
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "Do you think that others of our kind are any different?  Count them, "
#| "<CHARNAME>, and think of the multitudes of Bhaalspawn that existed and "
#| "brought misery to others, if not by intent, then even by their very "
#| "presence.  Would you allow such carnage to continue?  Have we not spared the"
#| " entire land from agony by the slaying of our siblings?"
msgid ""
"Do you think that others of our kind are any different? Count them, "
"<CHARNAME>, and think of the multitudes of Bhaalspawn that existed and "
"brought misery to others, if not by intent, then even by their very "
"presence. Would you allow such carnage to continue? Have we not spared the "
"entire land from agony by the slaying of our siblings?"
msgstr ""
"Denkt Ihr, dass andere Eurer Art besser wären?  Zählt sie, <CHARNAME>, und "
"denkt an die Heerscharen von Bhaalkindern, die existierten und anderen Leid "
"brachten, wenn nicht mit Absicht, so doch durch ihre bloße Gegenwart.  "
"Würdet Ihr erlauben, dass dieses Schlachten weitergeht?  Haben wir nicht das"
" ganze Land aus Qualen befreit, indem wir unsere Geschwister umbrachten?"

#: balth.tra:1179
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "You believe yourself to be the master of your destiny, do you?  The destiny "
#| "foreseen long ago by Alaundo?  You believe it by choice alone that you ended"
#| " up here, in this place?"
msgid ""
"You believe yourself to be the master of your destiny, do you? The destiny "
"foreseen long ago by Alaundo? You believe it by choice alone that you ended "
"up here, in this place?"
msgstr ""
"Ihr haltet Euch selbst für den Herrn Eures Schicksals, oder?  Des "
"Schicksals, das Alaundo vor langer Zeit vorhersah?  Ihr glaubt, dass Ihr "
"allein aufgrund Eurer Entscheidung hier, an diesem Ort, gelandet seid?"

#: balth.tra:1180
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "You mistake the path for the journey, my friend.  Whatever paths you have "
#| "taken since leaving Candlekeep, the journey has ended here as it was always "
#| "meant to.  Destiny masters us... we do not master it."
msgid ""
"You mistake the path for the journey, my friend. Whatever paths you have "
"taken since leaving Candlekeep, the journey has ended here as it was always "
"meant to. Destiny masters us... we do not master it."
msgstr ""
"Ihr verwechselt den Weg mit der Reise, mein Freund.  Welche Wege auch immer "
"Ihr gegangen seid, seit Ihr Kerzenburg verlassen habt, Eure Reise ist hier "
"zu Ende, wie es schon immer geplant war.  Das Schicksal beherrscht uns... "
"wir beherrschen es nicht."

#: balth.tra:1181
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "Yes, whether they were obstacles to be overcome or merely by-standers "
#| "crossing your path.  My own life has been little different, no matter how I "
#| "have struggled against it.  I am glad you see this... it will make things "
#| "much easier."
msgid ""
"Yes, whether they were obstacles to be overcome or merely by-standers "
"crossing your path. My own life has been little different, no matter how I "
"have struggled against it. I am glad you see this... it will make things "
"much easier."
msgstr ""
"Ja, ob sie nun Hindernisse darstellten, die Ihr überwinden musstet, oder nur"
" Unbeteiligte, die Euren Weg kreuzten.  Mein eigenes Leben war nicht viel "
"anders, gleich wie sehr ich dagegen ankämpfte.  Ich bin froh, dass Ihr das "
"erkennt... es macht die Dinge viel einfacher."

#: balth.tra:1182
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "You sound like Yaga-Shura, a giant in ego as well as body.  Yet he fell, "
#| "too, when his fate came due.  The power of your blood may yet make you "
#| "victorious, it is true, but the fact that you embrace the taint within you "
#| "makes my own path that much the clearer."
msgid ""
"You sound like Yaga-Shura, a giant in ego as well as body. Yet he fell, too,"
" when his fate came due. The power of your blood may yet make you "
"victorious, it is true, but the fact that you embrace the taint within you "
"makes my own path that much the clearer."
msgstr ""
"Ihr klingt wie Yaga-Shura, mit einem riesenhaften Ego und Körper.  Doch auch"
" er ist gefallen, als sein Schicksal sich erfüllte. Die Macht Eures Blutes "
"mag Euch den Sieg bringen, das ist wahr, aber dass Ihr den Makel in Euch "
"selbst annehmt, macht meinen Weg umso klarer."

#: balth2.tra:1002
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "<CHARNAME> does not stand alone, Melissan.  It is time that this is ended."
msgid ""
"<CHARNAME> does not stand alone, Melissan. It is time that this is ended."
msgstr ""
"<CHARNAME> steht nicht alleine, Melissan.  Es ist Zeit dieses nun zu "
"beenden."

#: balth2.tra:1003
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "I see well enough now, priestess.  Speak clever wit if you wish, you cannot "
#| "hope to defeat us."
msgid ""
"I see well enough now, priestess. Speak clever wit if you wish, you cannot "
"hope to defeat us."
msgstr ""
"Ich sehe nun klar genug, Priesterin.  Was immer Ihr auch sagen mögt, Ihr "
"könnt niemals hoffen, uns zu besiegen."

#: balth2.tra:1004
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "To return the essence to our father.  And great bloodshed in his name to "
#| "call him forth.  And I never believed it."
msgid ""
"To return the essence to our father. And great bloodshed in his name to call"
" him forth. And I never believed it."
msgstr ""
"Um die Essenz zu unserem Vater zurückzubringen.  Und ein großes Blutbad in "
"seinem Namen, um ihn hervorzurufen. All das habe ich niemals geglaubt."

#: balth2.tra:1005
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "We must be careful now, <CHARNAME>.  Within that stream of energy, Melissan "
#| "is invulnerable to harm... and I doubt she will come out of it willingly to "
#| "face us."
msgid ""
"We must be careful now, <CHARNAME>. Within that stream of energy, Melissan "
"is invulnerable to harm... and I doubt she will come out of it willingly to "
"face us."
msgstr ""
"Wir müssen jetzt vorsichtig sein, <CHARNAME>.  In diesem Strom der Energie "
"ist Melissan unverwundbar... und ich bezweifle, dass sie freiwillig heraus "
"kommt, uns zu helfen."

#: balth2.tra:1006
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "I think the essence pools that adjoin the Throne might be divertable by "
#| "someone with a connection to the essence.  A Bhaalspawn, one of us.  If all "
#| "three were cut off from her stream, Melissan might be forced to deal with us"
#| " rather than soak up even more power."
msgid ""
"I think the essence pools that adjoin the Throne might be divertable by "
"someone with a connection to the essence. A Bhaalspawn, one of us. If all "
"three were cut off from her stream, Melissan might be forced to deal with us"
" rather than soak up even more power."
msgstr ""
"Ich denke, dass die Essenzbecken in der Nähe des Throns umgelenkt werden "
"könnten, von jemandem, der eine Verbindung zur Essenz hat.  Einem Nachkommen"
" Bhaals, einem von uns.  Wenn alle drei von ihrem Strom abgeschnitten "
"würden, wäre Melissan gezwungen, sich mit uns zu beschäftigen, anstatt immer"
" mehr Macht aufzusaugen."

#: balth2.tra:1007
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "She has, no doubt, guarded the pools in some fashion... but it is the only "
#| "way to continue that I can think of.  Short of standing here and watching "
#| "her become a goddess, that is."
msgid ""
"She has, no doubt, guarded the pools in some fashion... but it is the only "
"way to continue that I can think of. Short of standing here and watching her"
" become a goddess, that is."
msgstr ""
"Sie hat die Becken zweifellos irgendwie bewacht... aber es ist der einzige "
"Weg, der mir einfällt.  Außer natürlich hier herumzustehen und zuzusehen, "
"wie sie eine Göttin wird."

#: balth2.tra:1008
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "You are a fool, Melissan.  You should have kept what divine energy you had "
#| "for yourself and not spread it amongst such servants.  It will prove your "
#| "doom."
msgid ""
"You are a fool, Melissan. You should have kept what divine energy you had "
"for yourself and not spread it amongst such servants. It will prove your "
"doom."
msgstr ""
"Ihr seid ein Narr, Melissan.  Ihr hättet Eure göttliche Energie für Euch "
"behalten sollen, anstatt sie unter solchen Sklaven aufzuteilen.  Dieses wird"
" Euer Untergang sein."

#: balth2.tra:1009
#, fuzzy
#| msgid "You... you are so beautiful.  I... had no idea..."
msgid "You... you are so beautiful. I... had no idea..."
msgstr "Ihr... Ihr seid so wunderschön.  Ich... hatte ja keine Ahnung..."

#: balth2.tra:1010
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "Choose?  You mean... I may rid myself of the taint on my soul forever?"
msgid "Choose? You mean... I may rid myself of the taint on my soul forever?"
msgstr ""
"Wählen?  Ihr meint... ich könnte mich von dem Makel auf meiner Seele für "
"immer befreien?"

#: balth2.tra:1011
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "And there is nothing that I ever wanted more.  I choose to become a mortal "
#| "gladly, and with all my heart.  To walk the earth without that dark burden "
#| "twisting my soul... I... I cannot even imagine..."
msgid ""
"And there is nothing that I ever wanted more. I choose to become a mortal "
"gladly, and with all my heart. To walk the earth without that dark burden "
"twisting my soul... I... I cannot even imagine..."
msgstr ""
"Da ist nichts, was ich mir jemals mehr gewünscht habe.  So wähle ich gerne, "
"ein Sterblicher zu sein.  Auf der Erde zu leben ohne die dunkle Last, die "
"meine Seele einschnürt... ich... ich kann es noch gar nicht glauben..."

#: balth2.tra:1012
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "I cannot thank you enough, <CHARNAME>, for the gift you have given me.  I "
#| "once thought I had done everything I could to fight for what was good... but"
#| " it was you that showed me how wrong I was.  Without you, I would have died "
#| "with that stain upon my soul and perhaps even been Melissan's puppet "
#| "forever."
msgid ""
"I cannot thank you enough, <CHARNAME>, for the gift you have given me. I "
"once thought I had done everything I could to fight for what was good... but"
" it was you that showed me how wrong I was. Without you, I would have died "
"with that stain upon my soul and perhaps even been Melissan's puppet "
"forever."
msgstr ""
"Ich kann Euch nicht genug danken, <CHARNAME>, für das, was Ihr für mich "
"getan habt.  Ich dachte einst, ich hätte alles in meiner Macht getan, um für"
" das Gute zu kämpfen... aber Ihr ward es, der mir zeigte, wie falsch ich "
"lag.  Ohne Euch wäre ich mit diesem Makel auf meiner Seele gestorben und "
"vielleicht in alle Ewigkeit Melissans Marionette."

#: balth2.tra:1013
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "I cannot pretend to know what you are thinking, now, of the decision you "
#| "must make.  Nor do I pretend to certainty that the taint would bring such a "
#| "<PRO_MANWOMAN> such as yourself towards evil.  Perhaps you would overcome "
#| "that taint and be a good god, I cannot say."
msgid ""
"I cannot pretend to know what you are thinking, now, of the decision you "
"must make. Nor do I pretend to certainty that the taint would bring such a "
"<PRO_MANWOMAN> such as yourself towards evil. Perhaps you would overcome "
"that taint and be a good god, I cannot say."
msgstr ""
"Ich kann nicht behaupten, dass ich weiß, wie Ihr jetzt über die "
"Entscheidung, die Ihr nun treffen müsst, denkt.  Auch bin ich mir nicht "
"sicher, dass der Makel des Bhaal einen Mann wie Euch schließlich doch zum "
"Bösen verführen wird.  Vielleicht könnt Ihr den Makel überwinden und ein "
"guter Gott sein... ich weiß es nicht."

#: balth2.tra:1014
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "I just ask you to consider how Bhaal's taint has affected your life to this "
#| "point.  Do you really wish to have all of it?  What type of person actually "
#| "wishes to become a god?  Sarevok?  Irenicus?  Melissan?  Even if your "
#| "intentions are good, what of an eternity being chained to such power?"
msgid ""
"I just ask you to consider how Bhaal's taint has affected your life to this "
"point. Do you really wish to have all of it? What type of person actually "
"wishes to become a god? Sarevok? Irenicus? Melissan? Even if your intentions"
" are good, what of an eternity being chained to such power?"
msgstr ""
"Bedenkt jedoch, wie Bhaals Makel Euer Leben bis zu diesem Zeitpunkt "
"beeinflusst hat.  Wollt Ihr wirklich alles haben?  Welche Art von Mensch "
"wünscht tatsächlich ein Gott zu sein?  Sarevok?  Irenicus?  Melissan?  "
"Selbst wenn Eure Absichten gut sind, wollt Ihr auf ewig an solche Macht "
"gefesselt sein?"

#: balth2.tra:1015
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "The choice is your own.  You know yourself better than I.  I simply ask that"
#| " you consider the life you might have led, the mortal life, had the taint "
#| "never visited itself upon you back at Candlekeep.  I look forward to my own."
msgid ""
"The choice is your own. You know yourself better than I. I simply ask that "
"you consider the life you might have led, the mortal life, had the taint "
"never visited itself upon you back at Candlekeep. I look forward to my own."
msgstr ""
"Ihr müsst Eure Wahl treffen.  Ihr kennt Euch selbst besser als ich.  Jedoch "
"denkt darüber nach, wie Euer Leben vielleicht verlaufen wäre, Euer "
"sterbliches Leben, hätte Euch der Makel nicht heimgesucht in Kerzenburg.  "
"Ich jedenfalls freue mich auf mein neues Leben."

#: balth2.tra:1016
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "And so it is done.  I believe you have made the right choice.  I look "
#| "forward to meeting you again on FaerÃ»n, <CHARNAME>...as a mortal and a true"
#| " <PRO_BROTHERSISTER>."
msgid ""
"And so it is done. I believe you have made the right choice. I look forward "
"to meeting you again on Faerun, <CHARNAME>...as a mortal and a true "
"<PRO_BROTHERSISTER>."
msgstr ""
"Nun ist es vollbracht.  Ich glaube, Ihr habt die richtige Entscheidung "
"getroffen.  Ich freue mich, Euch in Faerûn wieder zu treffen, <CHARNAME>... "
"als Sterblichen und wahren Bruder."

#: balth2.tra:1017
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "And so you take the road less traveled, <CHARNAME>.  I cannot say I envy "
#| "you.  I hope the power brings you what you expect and desire, my friend.  "
#| "When I look up at the heavens and see the brightest star in the sky, I shall"
#| " think of you and offer a prayer."
msgid ""
"And so you take the road less traveled, <CHARNAME>. I cannot say I envy you."
" I hope the power brings you what you expect and desire, my friend. When I "
"look up at the heavens and see the brightest star in the sky, I shall think "
"of you and offer a prayer."
msgstr ""
"Und so nehmt Ihr einen Weg, den wenige bisher beschritten haben, <CHARNAME>."
"  Ich kann nicht sagen, dass ich Euch beneide.  Ich hoffe, die Macht bringt "
"Euch das, was Ihr erwartet und wünscht, mein Freund.  Wenn ich in den Himmel"
" schaue und dort den hellsten Stern erblicke, so werde ich an Euch denken "
"und für Euch beten."

#: balth2.tra:1018
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "Melissan keeps restoring her immortal energies at the fount!  There must be "
#| "a way to weaken her further, or we will never defeat her!"
msgid ""
"Melissan keeps restoring her immortal energies at the fount! There must be a"
" way to weaken her further, or we will never defeat her!"
msgstr ""
"Melissan stellt immer noch ihre unsterblichen Energien an der Quelle wieder "
"her! Es muss einen Weg geben, sie noch mehr zu schwächen, oder wir werden "
"sie nie besiegen!"

#: balth2_ee.tra:1016
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "And so it is done.  I believe you have made the right choice.  I look "
#| "forward to meeting you again on FaerÃ»n, <CHARNAME>...as a mortal and a true"
#| " <PRO_BROTHERSISTER>."
msgid ""
"And so it is done. I believe you have made the right choice. I look forward "
"to meeting you again on Faerûn, <CHARNAME>...as a mortal and a true "
"<PRO_BROTHERSISTER>."
msgstr ""
"Nun ist es vollbracht.  Ich glaube, Ihr habt die richtige Entscheidung "
"getroffen.  Ich freue mich, Euch in Faerûn wieder zu treffen, <CHARNAME>... "
"als Sterblichen und wahren Bruder."

#: balth_ee.tra:1091
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "I have mastered the power within me and held the evil in check, but I know "
#| "as well... if not better... then most of my brethren the threat that it "
#| "holds for all of FaerÃ»n.  I will not allow this.  I have dedicated my life "
#| "to preventing it."
msgid ""
"I have mastered the power within me and held the evil in check, but I know "
"as well... if not better... then most of my brethren the threat that it "
"holds for all of Faerûn. I will not allow this. I have dedicated my life to "
"preventing it."
msgstr ""
"Ich habe die Macht in mir bezwungen und das Böse in Schach gehalten, aber "
"ich kenne genauso gut... wenn nicht besser... als meine Geschwister die "
"Gefahr, die es für ganz Faerûn darstellt.  Ich werde das nicht erlauben.  "
"Dies zu verhindern, ist der Sinn meines Lebens."

#: balth_ee.tra:1161
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "I make no judgement upon you, <CHARNAME>.  You are what you were born to be."
#| "  I can only trust myself to hold to the path of good that will lead to the "
#| "destruction of the true evil that threatens FaerÃ»n.  There is no other path"
#| " for me."
msgid ""
"I make no judgement upon you, <CHARNAME>. You are what you were born to be. "
"I can only trust myself to hold to the path of good that will lead to the "
"destruction of the true evil that threatens Faerûn. There is no other path "
"for me."
msgstr ""
"Ich richte Euch nicht, <CHARNAME>.  Ihr seid der, als der Ihr geboren "
"wurdet. Ich kann nur mir selbst vertrauen, dass ich auf dem Weg bleibe, der "
"zur Vernichtung des wahren Bösen führt, das Faerûn bedroht.  Es gibt keinen "
"anderen Weg für mich."

#: ee.tra:3001
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "Sarevok's Sword of Chaos\n"
#| "The blade of Sarevok, brother of <CHARNAME>, used in the battle they fought in faraway Baldur's Gate. <CHARNAME> prevailed, destroying Sarevok's plans and rescuing the Sword Coast from the brink of war. Now Sarevok has joined with <CHARNAME>'s cause and his blade has been restored to him. Sarevok describes the weapon as a Deathbringer blade and has restored some of the weapon's old power.  Without his Bhaalspawn essence to channel through the sword, however, it cannot achieve the power it once had. Still, however, it is a formidable weapon...and one that Sarevok warns would become increasingly difficult to wield in the hands of one who was not a Deathbringer, if they could use it at all.\n"
